For more on this, we speak to Political analysts Levy Ndou and David Maimela, and Sizwe SamaYende, a journalist who is very close to matters therein Mpumalanga. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Mandla Ndlovu has been elected the new chairperson of the ANC in Mpumalanga. Ndlovu defeated Lucky Ndinisa who received only 278 votes. Speedy Mashilo wins the Deputy Chairperson position with 505 votes. New Deputy Provincial Secretary is Lindiwe Ntshalintshali with 458 votes. Muzi Chirwa is the provincial secretary, he defeated Pat Ngomane. The provincial treasurer is Mandla Msibi with 452 votes. 